My family and I went to this restaurant location the other day. We got seated at a dirty table and we could see dust on the floor. Then our waitress came and spilled salsa, nearly getting some on my mom. Instead of grabbing cleaning products, she picks up two semi clean towels and scrapes the salsa off the table before barely “cleaning” it with another towel. There were still streaks from where the salsa was. Then there were the dirty bathrooms. It looked like it hadn’t been cleaned in a while. Cobwebs in the corners and there was also liquid on the floor near the toilet. I wasn’t sure if it was water or not. Now onto the food. I had gotten a chimichanga and it was so difficult to cut when I got it. My sister in law and mother also had difficulty with their dessert chimichangas to the point my sister in law just picked it up, it covered in chocolate sauce, and ate it by hand. Our waitress barely came by to check on us, ask us if we needed anything more to drink, left dirty plates at our table to the point it was crowding us. She also gave us dirty looks or scoffed when we asked for more napkins, chips, and tortillas for my mom’s fajita.  We do not feel comfortable coming back to this location at all.

I have been here multiple times and even attended an event here. I was looking to book the party room for 12-18 of this year. I was supposed to get married on that date and instead I wanted to host a would be celebration for my family and bridal party, on yes... that specific date. It is really the only thing I do not want to compromise on since it was supposed to be our special day. I spoke with Carlos, I asked for a quote for about 30 people. He responded and said that date wasn't available and they had other dates. I responded and said, "Oh man! Sorry, I was just really looking for that date only at the moment. Thanks for your help". To which he replied with a crying laughing emoji. Wasn't sure what was so funny about my email saying, thanks but no thanks.  But since he wanted to be extremely unprofessional, I decided to go full blown "Karen." I was a wedding coordinator for years, I know what it's like to have people want specific dates. All you have to say is, I'm sorry, If you change your mind let me know.  THANKS CARLOS TRUE FRIEND BRO!

The guacamole was more tomato-y and juicy, not smooth, tart, and thick and seemed not very fresh. The tortillas seemed to be not of the greatest/freshest quality, flavorless, and a little hard upon receipt. If you haven't been spoiled by real, freshly made Mexican food (including hand made/traditionally heated tortillas) both here and abroad (this is Tex-Mex), then this will suit your needs.
